<font color="#FF0000">EFFECTS OF THE YOUNG</font><br>
<tt>Tue Oct 21  9:00:29 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
my father was in the the war and if it's one thing I can say, it's that he was forever changed from it.  I love him very dearly but it is very hard to deal with his moods.  He has Post Traumatic War Syndrome (only just found out) Sometimes at night he has nightmares and it is hard to keep him in the living. <br>
I have tried to stop him many times from ending his life, but the time is fast approaching that I will no longer be around.  My mother has opted to divorce him because she feels that it is not healthy for my two younger brothers and sister are witness to his moods.<br>
I may not have been there, I may be only eighteen years old but I know what it is like to care for those who have.  I don't think the government every expected to have such lasting effects of this war.  May be with a little luck we will learn from this and take better precautions.                                                                                                                         
